{{Politics of Iceland}}
[[File:Mennta- og menningarmálaráðuneytið 2018.jpg|thumb|Ministry of Education, Science and Culture building in [[Reykjavík]] in 2018]]

The '''Ministry of Education, Science and Culture''' ({{lang-is|Mennta- og menningarmálaráðuneytið}}) is an [[Iceland]]ic [[Cabinet of Iceland|cabinet-level]] ministry founded 16 December 1942. The ministry is divided into three departments and four offices. The current [[Minister of Education, Science and Culture (Iceland)|Minister of Education, Science and Culture]] is [[Lilja Dögg Alfreðsdóttir]].

