'''''Ninety Percent of Everything: Inside Shipping, the Invisible Industry That Puts Clothes on Your Back, Gas in Your Car, And Food on Your Plate''''' is a book by [[Rose George]] about the international [[shipping industry]]. In 2013 the 287 page book was published in [[New York City]] by [[Metropolitan Books]], an imprint of [[Henry Holt and Company]].<ref name=garner> {{cite news | last = Garner | first =Dwight | title =Life on Ships That Make World Go Round: ‘Ninety Percent of Everything,’ by Rose George | newspaper = New York Times | location =NYC | date =October 16, 2013 | url =https://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/17/books/ninety-percent-of-everything-by-rose-george.html | accessdate =July 17, 2015}}</ref><ref name=tgross> {{cite news | last = Gross | first = Terry | title = Shipping: The 'Invisible Industry' That Clothes And Feeds You | newspaper = [[Fresh Air]] | format = Podcast | publisher =[[National Public Radio]] | date =August 14, 2013 | url =https://www.npr.org/2013/08/14/211981786/shipping-the-invisible-industry-that-clothes-and-feeds-you | accessdate =July 17, 2015 }}</ref><ref name=causey> {{cite news | last = Causey | first = Michael | title =Ninety Percent of Everything: Inside Shipping... | newspaper =Washington Review of Books | location =Washington, DC | pages = | language = | publisher = | date =August 13, 2013 | url =http://www.washingtonindependentreviewofbooks.com/bookreview/ninety-percent-of-everything-inside-shipping-the-invisible-industry | accessdate =July 17, 2015}}</ref>
