{{about|an American political consultant|the fictional doctor|Ryan Chamberlain (General Hospital)}}

'''Ryan Kelly Chamberlain II''' is an American media and political consultant, who worked on the campaign of [[Gavin Newsom]] in his run for mayor of San Francisco. He was the subject of a nationwide FBI search beginning May 31, 2014, after evidence of explosives were reportedly found in his San Francisco apartment, and after he had allegedly posted a suicide note on [[Facebook]]. Details of the reasons for the manhunt were not immediately released by investigators. Chamberlain was arrested by the FBI in the evening on Monday June 2, 2014 within the San Francisco city limits.<ref>[https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2014/06/01/fbi-man-hunt-explosives-ryan-kelly-chamberlain/9845131/]</ref><ref>[http://abcnews.go.com/US/explosives-suspect-ryan-chamberlain-custody-fbi/story?id=23968189]</ref><ref>[http://blog.sfgate.com/stew/2014/06/02/fbi-suspect-ryan-chamberlain-arrested-in-s-f/]</ref><ref>[http://www.sfbg.com/politics/2014/06/02/wanted-pr-consultant-ryan-chamberlain-burned-sf-politics]</ref> He was charged with possessing an illegal explosive device. Chamberlain allegedly had "four components necessary to comprise an IED" in his apartment, according to the [[Federal Bureau of Investigation|FBI]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-chamberlain-charges-filed-press-20140603-story.html |title=Ryan Chamberlain had makings of bomb in S.F. apartment, FBI says |publisher=latimes.com |date=2014-06-03 |first=Joseph |last=Serna |accessdate=2014-06-04}}</ref>

